To all potential university partners in agricultural research, Please read the attached letter from Nora Lapitan, Research Division Chief in theÂ Bureau for Food Security, announcing the upcoming Feed the Future Innovation Lab for Crop Improvement. This new Feed the Future Innovation Lab will focus on tool and method development to support partner-country breeding efforts of targeted "product profiles" in selected crops: legumes, sorghum, millet, roots, tubers, and bananas. In a few weeks, the Notice of Funding Opportunity will be posted to Grants.gov, so please check that site frequently so that you do not miss it!